        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 6:24PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 624 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms 7
miles south of O'Donnell, or 11 miles northeast of Lamesa. These
thunderstorms were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Punkin Center, Hancock, and Arvana.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
